name: Clean & Private Family Guest Suite near the Beach
description:
Unwind on the private patio & experience the ocean view or enjoy your family & friends around the table in the cozy living room. Near the beach & tourist attractions, this private & comfortable guest suite features a full kitchen, a full bath & family friendly amenities in the modern & stylish comforts of home. Our suite has been completely remodeled and comfortably furnished. It includes a private entrance, 2 bedrooms each with a queen bed, 1 bathroom with shower and tub, 1 full kitchen with stove, fridge and sink, living/dining room with entertainment center and WIFI with 100+Mbps download speeds.

We live in the floor above and are av

host_about: I love the ocean, living by it, traveling to explore it, and playing in the waves.  Ive always lived close the beach; Ojai, Santa Cruz and San Francisco are the places I've called home. Now I get to share these passions with my lovely wife Meghan and my beautiful daughter Evelyn.  In addition to enjoying our home, we also love to travel.  We've been to several locations in Mexico, Belize, Hawaii,  Costa Rica, Peru, Thailand and Myanmar.  I don't expect that our travel list is close to being complete.  One day we hope to travel to Indonesia for surf and scuba.  While the adventures we've had while traveling are fun, the people we've met along the way make our experience truely remarkable.  Hopefully, someday in the future we'll meet you (the reader) and create a story worth telling.  Until then, love and happiness.

name: Soak Up Historic Charm at the Inner Sunset Getaway
description:
Gather around the cozy brick fireplace for evening chats in the stately wood paneled great room. Built in 1914, the Edwardian era building maintains its classic architecture while modern renovations, including sleek cabinetry, quartz counters, a spacious glass enclosed shower and a calm colour palette of cool grays, bring the period space up to date.

The spacious guest suite is over 1300 square feet in size. With windows on 4 sides of the building, light pours into the space.
neighborhood_overview: The Airbnb is located in SF's Inner Sunset neighborhood which is packed with diverse eateries, stores and more. Grandview Park is a few blocks from the house, with panoramic views of both San Francisco and Marin, including the Golden Gate Bridge, downtown San Francisco, and the Pacific Ocean. Golden Gate Park is just a few blocks from the Airbnb with attractions such as Japanese Tea Garden, Academy of Science and De Young Fine Art Museum.
host_about: Our family loves San Francisco and hopes you do too!  We have two young children and love exploring the city with them. With lots of great shops nearby in the Inner Sunset, we often make our way to Irving street for Easy Breezy frozen yogurt or a visit to the magic shop.

Beautiful big Victorian in Noe Valley, one of the most popular, cleanest, safest, accessible neighborhoods of SF. Easy stroll to restaurants, shops, cafes, Sat. farmers market, Whole Foods, kids parks, Dolores Park, Castro, Mission & public transportation.

*(PLEASE BE AWARE THE 3RD BEDROOM IS CONSIDERED A DEN/office, as it is tandem to the main upper bedroom (one must cross through it to access the main upper bedroom.)

neighborhood_overview: Noe valley is one of the best neighborhoods in San Francisco. It is considered one of the safest family friendly, and cleanest neighborhoods in SF. Very good places to eat just around the corner, Whole foods is two blocks away. Doughnut shop on the next corner is open 24 hours a day, cafes, public transit all close by. There is no need for a car generally, most essentials a a short stroll away, and there are Muni trains , Bart and buses very close as well.

name: Urban Chic in Lower Pacific Heights
description:
Long term deals! Ideally located in Lower Pacific Heights just 2 blocks from vibrant Fillmore Street’s world class restaurants & boutiques. 2 bedroom 1 bath private suite on lower level with large living area and kitchenette in an historic Victorian home built in 1879. Walk to Lafayette & Alta Plaza parks. Close to bus lines. Easy access to Union Square, financial district, SOMA, Golden Gate Park & Sacramento St. corridor.

Home is professionally cleaned and hospital-grade disinfected.
neighborhood_overview: Being located in Lower Pacific Heights just two blocks from Fillmore Street makes this an A+ location for any and all who want an urban experience in the center of San Francisco.  If you prefer to start your day at a cafe, The Fillmore Bake Shop is two blocks away. Their pastries are sublime. If you want a bigger breakfast, walk up the street to Jane's where their morning egg dishes are the rave of the city. Head out to see the rest of the city and then dine on the Fillmore at night. Lots of good shopping. Close to all things you'd want to see in San Francisco.

This safe, quiet neighborhood in the hills of SF is a short walk from McLaren Park where you can enjoy a hike or long run, find a natural spring, and take in views of the Bay Area.

This location is quiet and private, but it's about a 1 mile walk to restaurants, so usually you'll start your adventures with a short car ride. San Francisco is a small city, and you can go anywhere in a few minutes by car, traffic permitting. You can drive to the Golden Gate Bridge in as little as 20 minutes if you get up early. Best to plan your travel during non-commute hours.

Getting around is easy. Car services arrive so fast you have to be ready when you call. Buses run nearby that go nice places.

Cayuga Playground park is just a few minutes walk down the street and is worth a visit. Considered to be one of San Francisco’s hidden gems. neighborhood_overview:
Sunnyside is a quiet, family-oriented neighborhood located just south of Twin Peaks. Peaceful in the early mornings and at night.

1. Enjoy walking or biking in the hills that occupy nearby Westwood, Monterey Heights, and St. Francis Woods.
2. Eat or shop at nearby West Portal, Ocean Avenue, or Glen Park.
3. A Safeway is open late is located on the same block.
4. Whole Foods is a 3 minute drive away.
5. A pizza parlor is on the corner.
6. Railroad Espresso is two blocks away.
7. A string of restaurants line adjacent Monterey Boulevard.
8. Stonestown Galleria, a major mall, is a 10 minute drive away.
9. A playground is a block away, Sunnyside Playground is 3 blocks away, and Sunnyside Conservatory is a 8 minute walk.

host_about:
Where you stay while visiting a city directly impacts your perceptions of that city. At International Executive Rental (IER) we believe your accommodations should be on par with your environment, and since San Francisco is such an incredible city, your housing must be as well. Without mentioning the superb weather and fabulous restaurants, let’s be fair; there are multiple highlights in San Francisco that should be encountered, if you are looking for additional reasons to plan your next trip. description: A delightful bright home with three bedrooms (two queens and one twin), large kitchen to cook all your meals in and a comfortable living room to watch Friday night movies. neighborhood_overview:
Sunnyside is on the South West side of the city. Not far from the ocean so the weather can be cool and foggy. We are a 10 min. drive (longer on the bus 20 min.) to Ocean Beach, the zoo, Stern Grove, Lake Merced, Golden Gate Park, San Francisco Sate University, City College, Mt. Davidson, and more.

San Francisco is jam packed with places to explore, all within a bus ride or short drive.

The neighborhood is very quiet and neighbors are friendly. It is located near Ocean Ave. which has a Whole Foods and other shops and restaurants. There is a Safeway two blocks away on Monterrey Blvd. The other two neighborhoods that are close by are West Portal and Glen Park. There are two BART stations nearby - one at Glen Park and one at Balboa Station. There is a bus (the number 43) that goes from the corner of our street all the way across town. There is also a bus (number 23) on Monterrey that goes to the beach and zoo.
host_about: We are a recently retired couple looking forward to our free time and being able to travel again.  Serge is from France and we visit family there once a year.  We are also hoping to spend time with our daughter and grandson in Michigan where Nancy is originally from.  We have lived in San Francisco for over 40 years and consider it home.  There is so much to explore and discover in the area and in California and the West!  We are happy to share our home while we come and go from our travels.  We hope that you will care for our home as we do and enjoy your time while here.

Our "main street" Cortland Avenue has a little of everything, including several world class restaurants.

Right outside our door is Bernal Hill, a beautiful piece of parkland that affords a 360º view of San Francisco. If you are lucky you may see one of our local coyotes. Come here for sunrise, sunset or for star gazing!

Don't miss our Alemany Market which becomes one of our city’s best Farmers Markets on Saturdays and a Flea Market on Sundays.

PLEASE DO NOT LEAVE ANYTHING VISIBLE IN YOUR CAR. UNFORTUNATELY SMASH AND GRABS ARE A REGULAR OCCURRENCE EVERYWHERE IN SAN FRANCISCO.
host_about:
I'm Jeannie, my husband, Skate and I have lived in San Francisco for 40+ years. 
We have travelled throughout Europe, Asia, Middle East, Africa & Central, North & South America & French Polynesia.  
We enjoy traveling simply, spending time in our garden & with our four children. We love live music which you may hear Skate playing!
Airbnb is a great way to travel but also a way to meet new people from all over the world while staying at home!

name: Peaceful Noe Home with Office and Patio by 24th Street
description:
Welcome to a quiet oasis in Noe!

Noe Valley Luxury Modern is both a family and business traveler friendly space located in a fully rebuilt house that turned a single family cottage from the 1880's into a contemporary multi-level home built for this millennium's lifestyle. High-end finishes and amenities throughout, wonderful indoor-outdoor living spaces, and virtually everything you could possibly need within 2-5 blocks. Think urban boutique hotel - but with a LOT more space!
neighborhood_overview: The home is on a quiet residential street, just off lively 24th Street. It’s an easy walk to everything from Whole Foods and corner burritos, to neighborhood bars and upscale dining. The Noe Valley Saturday Farmers’ Market runs year-round.
host_about:
Andy is a life-long traveler, thrilled to finally be back home in the Bay Area where he grew up and where his extended family still resides.  In 2008 Andy and his wife Tanya were fortunate to find a classic Noe Valley fixer-upper and moved into the cute, tiny Pioneer Victorian where they lived for almost 6 years.  In 2013 they began a complete reconstruction of the 1880's cottage and in 2014 moved their family back into a completely transformed contemporary house equipped for this millenium's lifestyle - the Victorian front remains, but everything behind it now meets the needs and expectations of today (hello, closets and gigabit ethernet...).  Andy has been an at-home Dad since 2000, and has worked in tourism, academia, and as a professional chef.  He loves the vibrant food culture in San Francisco and only wishes he had more time to take advantage of all the amazing arts that San Francisco dishes up on a daily basis as well as the wonderful outdoor spaces, hikes, and bike rides that are nearby.  Andy is very knowledgeable about San Francisco food and fun and is happy to make suggestions to help your stay be enjoyable, fun and tasty, whether you are here for business or family pleasure.

Andy has enjoyed a wide variety of travel styles and accommodations over the years, from $3/night huts on beaches in Eastern Indonesia, simple Ryokan in Japan, and luxury hotels and chateaux in the US, Asia and Europe: the apartment is equipped to closely match the experience of a boutique hotel - luxury finishes throughout and thoughtful amenities - but with a lot more space than most boutique hotels provide!

description: Enjoy your fully furnished flat atop sunny POTRERO HILL. Satisfy all your travel needs here--an exceptional fully remodeled sun-lit Victorian. WOW! Panoramic sunset view of Twin Peaks, the Golden Gate Bridge, Mt. Tam, & Mission. Mesmerizing famous SF fog boils over TwinPeaks--an experience UNIQUE to Potrero Hill's west edge. Socialize with family & friends in your spacious flat. Explore SF from a central location. Enjoy cable TV & WiFi. EASY street parking, transportation, safe neighborhood.
neighborhood_overview: We are located across the street from a charming Community Garden and less than half a block from a hilltop park and play ground with views of Twin Peaks, the Golden Gate Bridge and Mt.Tamilpais.  Potrero Hill is famous for its panoramic city and Bay views and its sunny warm weather.  The location is perfect--only minutes from downtown, financial center, Moscone Center, Civic Center, museums, SF Giants ballpark, Warriors Stadium, and close to the airport as well. Potrero Hill is home to excellent restaurants, shops, cafes, and Whole Foods Market(Rhode Island St. btwn Mariposa & 17th St.   Steep hill). Safeway super market(Potrero & 16th St. take the footbridge at 18th & San Bruno.  Steep hill.) is also nearby.  Closest grocery is Chiotra's Deli on Rhode Island btwn 20th and Southern Heights.  the route is mostly flat).  Potrero Hill is within walking distance to the Mission District, SOMA, and Dog Patch neighborhoods.
host_about:
AnneKarin was born in Chicago to Henry P. and Elly Glass.  Theirs was an artistic household.  Henry was educated in the Wiener Werkstadt and was one of the founders of the field of Industrial Design in the U.S.  Elly was a member of the Viennese Dressmakers’ Guild.  Both of them taught at the School of the Art Institute of Chicago.  AnneKarin grew up in Northfield IL and graduated from New Trier HS in 1961.  She received her BA in Anthropology from the University of Illinois, Urbana, in 1966 and joined the Peace Corps that same year.  She served as a Volunteer for three years in Ilheus, Bahia, Brazil, where she founded a leather working factory that provided steady work for local shoe makers.  Upon her return she went to Illinois Institute of Technology where she received an MA in Linguistics.
She tolerated the weather in Chicago until 1973 when she moved to San Francisco where Peace Corps friends facilitated her settlement into a new life on the West Coast.  Two months after she arrived she broke her leg in a ski accident and spent 11 months in a cast.  When able to walk again, she pursued a sign painting business which grew into a brokerage for architectural graphics.  From that she moved into print brokering, specializing in 3-D displays.  This enabled her to buy the house she was living in on Potrero Hill in San Francisco.
The recession in 1989 plus the introduction of computer technology into the world of print created a crossroad.  AnneKarin decided to give up the printing business and return to graduate school where she earned a graduate certificate in Educational Therapy.  She specialized in perception/cognition and opened a private practice, helping children and adults with learning disabilities to address the underlying causes of their learning problems.  
During all these years AnneKarin continued to pursue visual art.  Today she works as an artist, focusing on the figure.  When no model is available she enjoys painting still lifes, abstracts, and landscapes.  She has shown her work internationally and in many competitions across the U.S.  She is a member of the Artists’ Guild of San Francisco.
AnneKarin lives with Clebia, whom she met in Ilheus when she was a Peace Corps volunteer. Clebia is a case worker for intellectually challenged adults and a gourmet cook.  Clebia and AnneKarin enjoy travel, walking in the outdoors, fine dining, music, the ballet, who done-its, and old and new friendships.

host_about:
Hi, I'm Doug! As a native of San Francisco, I attended SF's Lowell High School and graduated from UC Berkeley with a degree in Molecular Cell Biology and a minor in German.  I'm a huge Bay Area sports fan, and I try to go to the gym at least twice a week!

During college, while studying abroad in Germany for a year, I took the opportunity to fly and to rail to 10 of the neighboring European countries.  I've also spent some time traveling solo in South East Asia.  I really enjoy immersing myself in different cultures as I find the challenge especially rewarding.  I can understand and speak a little German still.  My Mandarin is embarrassingly poor.

I have been an Airbnb Superhost manager for my family's two room in-law in San Francisco since 2015, compiling more than 600 total reviews.  With this experience, I listed my own recently remodeled home on Airbnb here in the Excelsior district of SF, right off of Geneva Avenue and Mission Street.

I've really enjoyed the Airbnb hosting experience so far, and would like to invite you to your own super clean, modern, private space on the entire ground level floor of my home.  I look forward to hosting you!

host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview: Buena Vista Park is a park in the Haight-Ashbury and Buena Vista Heights neighborhoods of San Francisco, California. It is the oldest official park in San Francisco, established in 1867 as Hill Park, later renamed Buena Vista. It is bounded by Haight Street to the north, and by Buena Vista Avenue West and Buena Vista Avenue East. The park is on a steep hill that peaks at 575 feet (175 m), and covers 37 acres (150,000 m2). The lowest section is the north end along Haight.  Surrounded by Upper and Lower Haight, Cole Valley, and Duboce Triangle neighborhoods.

host_about:
I love spending my time in different places in the world. Coming from a Mediterranean culture and climate I enjoy living in California. On one hand you get walkable access to nature, wild life, hiking and mountain biking and on the other accessibility to top notch international foods from all around. 

I am an architect and a Qi Gong teacher. I teach in Marin and in SF. I enjoy Qi Gong, healing arts, health and fitness. I like art and architecture and appreciate our proximity to these. My love of the outdoors and nature and brought me to live here in this particular spot in California. I love to cook so I appreciate good food and access to great fresh organic produce, like here. The third largest farmers market in California is just few minutes drive away from our Marin San Rafael guest house.

Adam, my life partner, works in San Francisco in the tech industry and is a great cook and a gardener. We grow our own vegetables and raise bees and get our own honey on property in San Rafael CA. We would love for you to try it!

I would like to help you feel as comfortable as possible when here, so let me know what you need and feel free to ask me for local tips!

Drive 25 minutes to San Francisco or take a scenic ferry ride directly to San Francisco from Larkspur Landing without the hassle of parking your car when in San Francisco.

If you are a guest to our Palm Springs location home, Joshua Tree National Park, Many beautiful and shaded trail with waterfalls are around us like Murray Canyon Trail. Hike up the South Llyken Trail and watch the elusive wild Bighorn sheep.

If you are a swimmer, you are in heaven! our pool is heated and half olympic size!

neighborhood_overview: The Excelsior District has existed on San Francisco maps as far back as 1869, when the Excelsior Homestead Association filed a plat map with the city defining the neighborhood’s street grid and distinctive “around the world” street-naming pattern. Paris and Prague, Russia and Brazil, are all steps from each other on the avenues and streets held within the neighborhood’s boundaries of Silver and Geneva Avenues, Mission Street and McLaren Park. Close-knit Excelsior is among the oldest and most culturally diverse areas in San Francisco. Asian supermarkets, Mexican taquerias and Salvadoran bakeries line Mission Street, while colorful street art depicts the neighborhood's ethnic variety.

name: Glen Park pied-à-terre
description:
Welcome to my cozy home in Glen Park, where I’ve lived for over 30 years. This is a Goldilocks-sized two-bedroom, 1.5-bath home located in one of the most charming neighborhoods in San Francisco.

Glen Park has a grocery store, coffee shop, adorable restaurants nearby, a vast park, and easy access to public transportation, including BART access to downtown, both airports and the greater Bay Area. You are near the on-ramps to 280 and 101 for easy driving access.
neighborhood_overview:
I’ve found Glen Park to be the perfect place to enjoy a peaceful pace of life, while still feeling connected to the vibrant city of San Francisco. The neighborhood has a quaint, almost village-like feel that’s rare to find in while still being inside the city of San Francisco. With its quiet streets and welcoming community, it's easy to take morning walks through the neighborhood to Glen Canyon Park. The local library, just a short stroll away offers a cozy place to sit with a good book and enjoy the company of other residents.

The commercial hub around Bosworth and Diamond Streets has everything you would need. For Breakfast, you can start your day with a visit to Glen Park Café, formerly known as Tyger’s, where the friendly staff know the regular's orders: order a stack of fluffy pancakes and a hot cup of coffee. From there, it’s off to the Canyon Market for some fresh produce, and then perhaps a stop at Bird & Beckett, the local bookstore that feels more like a community
host_about: I’m Karen, a retired schoolteacher. I love spending time with my grandchildren, family, and friends. I’m a fan of history and books, especially fiction. I’m an avid traveler, and I’m passionate about exploring the many art museums here in San Francisco. I look forward to welcoming you into my home!

neighborhood_overview:
The Richmond is in many ways defined by its relation to the parks; bordered by Golden Gate Park on the south, the Pacific Ocean to the west, and Lincoln Park, Land's End, Mountain Lake Park and the Presidio of San Francisco to the north, bisected by the Presidio Greenbelt and with the Marin Headlands and the Golden Gate Bridge in full and clear view, the neighborhood, which is otherwise a simple but far-reaching grid, has a feeling of being encapsulated by nature. It is thus known as a safe, peaceful, serene, family neighborhood.

The Richmond is home to a vast affluent Chinese population and its commercial strips on Geary Blvd. and Clement Street are commonly referred to as the second Chinatown and boasts more highly rated Chinese restaurants than Chinatown itself. The Richmond also has deep Irish and Russian roots and has many Catholic and Orthodox churches.

name: New! Private ensuite, loft ceilings, heated floors
description:
Welcome to our home minutes away from the cute cafes and boutiques of Noe Valley. Here's what makes our space so special:

- Super high ceilings create a spacious feel
- Heated floors to keep your feet toasty
- Large windows with tons of natural light but equipped with blackout shades
- Queen bed with premium memory foam mattress and crazy soft sheets
- You'll have a Nespresso coffee maker, water kettle, mini fridge, and mini induction stove for your convenience

We are very excited to host you!
neighborhood_overview:
This neighborhood is undeniably one of the best in San Francisco. It's quiet, safe, and peaceful, and has the most charming main street (24th Street) of all the neighborhoods in San Francisco.

And it's just a stone's throw away from the entertainment in the adjacent Castro and the Mission neighborhoods. Uber and Lyft are everywhere and wait times are generally less than 5 min for a pick up.

Also nearby:

- Cute neighborhood feeling Whole Foods is a 15 min walk
- Several tech shuttle bus stops are a 15 min walk
- Spectacular Twin Peaks 360-degree vista point is a 20 min walk
host_about:
Born in Shanghai, raised in Virginia Beach, worked in Singapore for 6 years, and now based in San Fran (yeah I said it).

Traveling and eating my way through the world are my ultimate passions!  That's one of the reasons why I decided to work for a company where I can inspire travelers to explore this great wide world of ours and experience it like a local!

I like the big cities for their diversity in people, energetic airports and mass transit, unique architecture, rooftop vista points, cafe culture, and how could I forget the variety of nomz.  I don't care much for main street shopping or gridlock traffic.

I equally like the unbeaten path for the sense of adventure, learning the local way of life, being able to see more than 10 stars at night, and loving the fact that I'm a little blue dot in the middle of nowhere on G00gle maps.  I'm not a fan of mozzies or sunblock eye sting.

Besides traveling and eating the world, I keep an active lifestyle of hitting the gym and playing tennis and volleyball.  But please don't ask me to do any distance running.  

I live by the golden rule of mutual respect, and I also appreciate tidiness.  Your home is in good hands with me.  Smoke? No. Drink? Not so much.  Ohm nom nom? Oh hell yeah!!

:-) :-)

European in flavor with its hidden stairways and alleys. Almost every street gives you a different and spectacular angle of San Francisco's beautiful bay. This neighborhood is so centralized that you do not even need a car. Nearly everything is within a short walk.

Nob Hill is one of the most upscale central neighborhood in San Francisco, and its safe and quiet. host_about:
Where you stay while visiting a city directly impacts your perceptions of that city. At International Executive Rental (IER) we believe your accommodations should be on par with your environment, and since San Francisco is such an incredible city, your housing must be as well. Without mentioning the superb weather and fabulous restaurants, let’s be fair; there are multiple highlights in San Francisco that should be encountered, if you are looking for additional reasons to plan your next trip. But before you tour…

Remember International Executive Rental (IER) is a corporate relocation company, located in the heart of San Francisco and specializing in executive and exceptional temporary housing. Our holdings will suit your most distinctive tastes, whether your stay requires a short term or an open-ended lease.

IER provides some of the best extended-stay experiences in San Francisco. Taking great care of all parties, anticipating California landlords and visitors needs is what distinguishes IER. With each stay, we offer housekeeping, local phone, basic cable, electric utility* with exemplary delivery of services. International Executive Rental offers corporate apartments, spacious homes, urban lofts, as well as San Francisco Victorians. ….

name: Sunny Marina flat, half block to the water
description: Spacious 2-bdrm/2 bath flat to rent in the quaint Marina District. City and nature at your front door. Run, walk or bike to the beach, the Presidio or the Golden Gate Bridge. Near restaurants, bars, and boutiques of Chestnut Street. Easy (and flat!) walk to many attractions, including the Palace of Fine Arts, the Presidio, Fort Mason, Fisherman's Wharf, Crissy Field and the beach. Perfect launchpad to explore it all.
neighborhood_overview: The Marina is a picturesque San Francisco neighborhood sitting right on the Bay, equi-walking distance from urban and natural attractions. Boutique shopping, bars and restaurants are a couple blocks away on both Chestnut and Union streets. Walk to grocery stores, bookshops, ice cream parlors, the library and movie theaters. The Marina Green is a half block up the street, and from there folks get a stunning view of the San Francisco Bay, from the Golden Gate Bridge through Alcatraz. It's a short walk to the beach. Turn east and head to Fort Mason, Fisherman's Wharf and onto the Embarcadero. Turn west to The Palace of Fine Arts, Crissy Field, the Presidio, and right over the Golden Gate Bridge. Access to Wine Country couldn't be simpler—just head over the Golden Gate Bridge and explore.
host_about:
I love San Francisco and am happy you're here!  I'm a design geek, foodie, scuba diver, and podcast host. I keep an eye on SFJazz and the latest at SFMOMA and the DeYoung. Dim sum is my weakness. I've got lots of city favorites and they're all in my house binder. (Spoiler alerts: Ice Cream Bar, Namu Gaji, A16, Bi-Rite, Calistoga mud baths, Fanny the Supermutt and taking the hills by Vespa!) I love stepping outside to the Golden Gate Bridge, the Bay and a gourmet Dynamo Donut. 

I'm happy to help you have a fun and relaxing stay here by the Bay!

neighborhood_overview:
Check out Airbnb's guide to my neighborhood:

The Richmond District is a neighborhood in the northwest corner of San Francisco. It is sandwiched between the Presidio to the north and Golden Gate Park to the south. Its commercial strips, Geary Boulevard and Clement Street, are commonly referred to as San Francisco's second Chinatown and boast more highly rated Chinese restaurants than Chinatown itself. The Richmond is well-located for walking to Golden Gate Park and the Presidio, taking public transit (Muni) to the Financial District, as well as driving north to Marin County across the Golden Gate Bridge or south to the Peninsula and SFO down 19th Avenue.

Eater voted on SF's hottest neighborhood for dining

Thrillist ranked SF's Best Eating Neighborhoods
host_about: As a world traveler myself, I would like to welcome visitors to San Francisco and help them make the most out of their vacations.  Originally from Hong Kong and educated in the SF Bay Area, I have been calling San Francisco home since 2010.  I enjoy travel, play golf, ping pong and badminton.  I also like to hike the many trails and beaches around Presidio and Golden Gate Park, and to explore the many wonderful restaurants around my home.

neighborhood_overview:
The outer Richmond is an overlooked gem in San Francisco. You'll feel like you're in the country with all the natural beauty in walking distance. Then walk a few blocks in the other direction, and you're in the city. Restaurants,shops,museums,culture. Hop on MUNI or Uber anywhere in the city in minutes. The neighborhood is safe, quiet, and great for kids and dogs.

My favorite restaurants in walking distance: Shanghai House (award winning Chinese food,Dimsum), Marla Bakery (the Marla Bun is TDF), Cassava (new California), Miki Sushi, Pizetta 211 (pizza). There are a ton on Clement St. Geary, and Irving and many more I haven't tried. You won't be hungry.

Simple Pleasures Cafe roasts their own coffee. It's good and inexpensive. They have music at night, Jazz, folk,etc.
Vinyl has an open jam session with jazz.
Balboa Theater is a Deco gem with first run and art-house movies.
The SF zoo is a short drive or Uber.
Golden Gate Park is walking distance

description:

neighborhood_overview:
--Parkside Square & Bob Cheney Field (3 blocks)
My kid's favorite playground!

--Pine Lake Park (2 blocks)
This natural area with a valley & lake also offers trails & a wide range of migratory birds.

--Stern Grove Park: (~ 0.2miles)
It consists of several park sections including the Concert Meadow, the West Meadow, and Pine Lake Park. The grove's Pine Lake is one of three natural lakes in the city of San Francisco. Since 1938, there have been weekly concerts and performances in the outdoor amphitheater during the summer months. Supported entirely by contributions, the concerts have always been free to the public. Crowds have often exceeded 20,000 persons.
--San Francisco Zoo & Gardens (~1 miles)
Most of popular! The zoo housed more than one thousand individual animals, representing more than 250 species.

--Cafe & Restaurants (~0.3 miles)

Riverside Seafood Restaurant (Chinese)
Dumpling Kitchen (Chinese)
Ming's
host_about: As a host, we joined airbnb on January 1, 2020. We have lived in Sunset district over 18 years. It is one of safest areas of San Francisco. We moved in current house when my daughter was just two-month old. Our neighbors used to call her window baby as she was always sitting or standing on sofa in front the window toward the street. It was the only channel she learned the outside world when she couldn't walk. Time flies and she is in elementary school now.

description: Relax and unwind in this spacious & newly updated lower/ground level flat.  With neutral colors and textures, you'll have that hotel feel but much more space to lounge around. neighborhood_overview:
Two blocks to Golden Gate Park, one block to Irving Street shops and restaurants; steps to the N-Judah light rail line which provides direct access to downtown, the ballpark, and Caltrain; less than 10 minutes to Ocean Beach by the N-Judah line.

The Sunset District is San Francisco's best kept secret. It is CLEAN and SAFE and QUIET. You are about a half hour from the hustle and bustle of downtown (by car or public transport). Out here the streets are wider, the backyards bigger, and free parking is easy to find. People who like the outdoors love the location, especially for surfing, jogging, cycling, and hiking.

Typically the Sunset can be foggy in June and July, but is clear and beautiful most of the rest of the year. Fall is stellar. Yearly temperatures hover in the 60-65 degrees. Golden Gate Park is only 2 blocks north and is filled with absolutely everything you can imagine: free concerts, archery ranges, entertainment pools, beautiful gardens, a bison paddock

description: Come and stay at our completely remodeled 2BR/2BA museum inspired cozy home with a kitchen in this quietly nestled and lovely neighborhood of Laurel Heights! neighborhood_overview: Stay in this aesthetically modern and fully functional home located in an upscale, tranquil neighborhood of Laurel Heights that borders Pacific Heights and Jordan Park! Since the neighborhood is bordered on the north (California Street) and south (Geary Boulevard) by stores, cafes, and restaurants (not to mention one of the area’s biggest and best-staffed hospitals, UCSF), virtually everything one could need is a short walk away. The main shopping strip is between Spruce and Laurel on California Street (the appropriately named Laurel Village). Here are two grocers, one high-end (Bryan’s, noted for its fish and meats) the other less so (Cal-Mart, though it has a much-lauded produce department), plus the usual array of boutiques and chains: The Gap, Chico’s, Starbucks, Pasta Pomodoro, Walgreen’s, Standard 5&10 Ace Hardware. On-street metered parking here can be difficult, though a small lot on the back side of Laurel Village on Mayfair Drive is available to shoppers. The stretch of Geary

host_about:
Hello and welcome to our home! 

We are a young married couple who met in LA during our early 20's and have lived in the Bay Area since 2011. Jenn hails from LA, the land of flip-flops and sun, and earned her undergraduate degrees and MBA from UCLA. 

Eddie spent his childhood in Michigan battling the Northern winters and perfecting his black ice driving before heading out West in search of perfect waves. He earned his undergraduate degree from Penn State and his MBA from UCLA. We both work in the tech industry. 

We have a 2-year-old bundle of joy. She's an English, Golden Retriever who will welcome you with a kisses, smiles, and a dangerous tail wag that will make you feel like a million bucks when you walk through our door.

Our weekends and getaways are likely to involve new cities, a hiking trail, or camping!

neighborhood_overview: The Outer Sunset district is the laid-back “beach town" of San Francisco. name: Beautiful 2 bed/2 bath - 1 block from Marina Blvd!
description: Welcome you to this Marina gem! Located in one of SF's best neighborhoods, and only one block from Marina Blvd, some of the City's most iconic destinations and outdoor attractions (Golden Gate Bridge, Palace of Fine Arts, Presidio, Fort Mason, Chrissy Fields, Marina Aquatic Park), and best dining spots (on Chestnut and Union St) are within a short walk of this flat. Pack your backpack with snacks from the Safeway grocery store a minute away, and start your day with a walk or jog along the water!
neighborhood_overview: This is by far one of the best neighborhoods! Views of the Golden Gate Bridge can be seen by walking 1 block north, and the Palace of Fine Arts is immediately west, while Fort Mason is immediately east. Explore Off the Grid on Friday nights and Sunday Farmer's Markets at Fort Mason (please check the schedules online beforehand).  Bike rental shops are near, as is the Safeway grocery store where you can find just about anything. Chestnut and Union Street offer great dining options for every palette, and this part of the City is flat making walking or jogging along the Bay and in the beautiful neighborhoods very popular. Street parking is easy to find, and best of all is that this is a very safe part of town!
host_about: Hi, my name is Leila and I am a Bay Area Native, fortunate to call San Francisco home for over the past 10 years. My passions include traveling, meeting new people, as well as giving back to my local community. I have lived in both Spain and Switzerland, and have travelled all throughout Europe, South America, and Asia, including parts of the Middle East. Some of my best memories and experiences are through the people I have met, and I hope to return this special exchange through hosting my home to visitors from all over the world. I look forward to meeting you, and making my home a special place for you to recall some great memories of your SF adventure!

description: Our historic 3 bedroom flat is sunny and spacious. Enjoy cooking in our fully equipped galley kitchen or dining out along the Valencia corridor, just half a block away.  A 7 minute walk takes you to either  historic streetcars or underground BART.
neighborhood_overview:
Our house is located within walking distance to everything you could ever need or desire! Cross the street and pick up a delicious, baked-in-house pastry and fresh drip coffee at Mission Beach Cafe. If you go on a weekday, the brunch cannot be missed! Weekends are busy unless you get there at 9am. Walk one block up to Dolores St. to pick up some groceries at the new Whole Foods or one block more to the Safeway. Take a 15 minute stroll along palm tree lined Dolores St.(very stroller friendly because sidewalks are wide) to Bi-Rite ice cream or pick up a sandwich at their store. Right next to Bi-rite is Tartine Bakery, with renowned buttery croissants and desserts. Take your picnic to Dolores park and enjoy the most gorgeous view of SF from the grassy hillside. Spend a few days walking along Valencia street, just a half block away from our house. There are so many restaurants, unique stores, and art galleries to be explored.

3 great parks are a short walk away for little ones.
host_about: We are a small family from San Francisco. We are clean, respectful, and very laid back. We have 2 small children and love to travel when we can. We used to be back-packers and hostel frequenters, but our kids and our aging backs don't like roughing it as much anymore. We love to eat and cook.

name: Family-Friendly Flat In San Francisco, CA. USA
description: Despite what you've heard or read, San Francisco remains an amazing town, that's once again reinventing itself.  A.I.'s  here so thank you for joining us for the next chapter.
neighborhood_overview:
GLEN PARK is really like a little village in the very center of the city. There are a variety of really good restaurants, from our authentic French bistro, Le P'tit Laurent, American fare at Chenery Park, Gialina Pizzeria, La Corneta Taqueria, Eco Sushi, and Osha Thai restaurant.

For breakfast, try Destination Bakery for fresh brioche, Tyger's Coffee Shop, or my favorite, Higher Grounds, where they serve amazing crepes.

The village has a great independent bookstore, the Bird & Beckett, and there’s live jazz on Friday and Sunday nights.

There’s a terrific gourmet supermarket, Canyon Market (see photos). Finally, the Village has its very own Farmer's Market on Sundays, selling local produce from farms all over the Bay Area. Yummmm!

GLEN CANYON PARK: Just one block from the flat is Glen Canyon Park. Unlike any other park in the City, it is situated in a rustic canyon, with 70 bucolic acres . There are easy walking trails along Islais C
host_about:

For the past 12 seasons, I've been an Airbnb host here a Maison Swiss, and it’s been a wonderful experience meeting folks from all over the world.  

My hundreds of five star reviews say it all

Red Sea Market is 5 minutes away and has great pizza, and a good selection of beers, chocolate, ice cream, and wine. Whole Foods is a relaxing 15-minute walk through the park.

Mission Street is a 10-minute walk and Glen Park is a 15-minute walk. There you will find some legendary bars and a plethora of restaurants. This is a booming area with wine bars popping up nearby and a brewpub that has live music most nights.

Between Chenery Street, Ocean Avenue, and Mission Street you may not need to go to the tourist San Francisco to experience life here.

neighborhood_overview: The Sunset is a unique demographic of surfers, dog lovers, and beach-goers. Typically the Sunset is foggy for June and July, but is clear most other days of the year.  Typical yearly temperatures hover in the 60-65 degrees Fahrenheit.  Our neighborhood is a friendly community, where most of us know each other by name and many natives still live in the area. The sunset district is like the "suburbs of the City", making it a more relaxed environment with all the benefits of a big city and entertainment at your fingertips.  Golden Gate Park (GGP) is within walking distance (1 mile) and holds the Outside Lands concert and the Hardly Strictly Bluegrass Festival. GGP also has the Academy of Science museum, De Young art museum, and Japanese Tea Garden. The Great Highway offers a beautiful 5 mile walking path from Sloat ave. to the Cliff House/Sutro Baths.  It is great for running, biking, walking. Popular restaurants include: Thanh Long, Outerlands, Underdogs Too, Beach Chalet & Brewery, Celi
host_about: We are native San Franciscans, work full time, enjoy the outdoors, camping, the beach, and enjoy wine with friends and family. I am particularly clean and love a comfortable home to relax in.  With roots from Hawaii, we try to live by the spirit of Aloha and the virtue of being honest and genuine with others.  We have traveled to exotic places around the world, including Bali, Costa Rica, Europe, Canada, Mexico, Japan and have visited over 20 U.S. states.  We love meeting new people and sharing our city life. Our lives are revolved around our children and raising a stable family in this fast paced city.  We frequent Lake Tahoe for skiing and snowboarding and Hawaii in the summer to visit family. Ocean beach is our front yard and is our haven for an extra breath. Constantly learning how to simplify and enjoy life is a focus.

name: Marina Motel Attached Rooms With Free Parking
description:
These two separate queen rooms connected by a large bathroom have their entrances in the back of our flower filled cobblestone courtyard. Each room has a Queen Size Bed with its own entrance door. The larger of the two rooms has a bistro table, chairs, small refrigerator, microwave, coffee maker and faces our neighbor's property. The smaller bedroom overlooks a small rooftop garden with our courtyard below. (Sleeps 2-4). This room is not pet friendly.
Maximum Guest Allowed: 4 Guests / Room
neighborhood_overview: San Francisco Marina District -The Marina District in named for its proximity to San Francisco's yacht harbors and the bay front walkway, but is known for its million dollar Mediterranean homes and its numerous restaurants and boutiques.The nearby Marina Green and Crissy Field are popular for jogging, windsurfing, and enjoying the spectacular views of the Golden Gate Bridge, Alcatraz and yachts sailing the Bay. Visit Chestnut Street for boutique shopping and alfresco dining.
host_about:
Built by the son of a California Gold Rush miner, the historic Marina Motel was built to celebrate the opening of the Golden Gate Bridge in the late 1930's and is still run by the same family. Ideally situated between Fisherman's Wharf and the Golden Gate Bridge in the popular Marina District, the Marina Motel offers a one-of-a-kind, old world experience. The first impression one has upon stepping into the motel's cobblestone courtyard is "Wow! This is like a little oasis back here with birds chirping, flowers EVERYWHERE, cute little garages and rooms decorated to feel like home. I feel like I'm in Europe."

Walk around the corner to the numerous outdoor cafes, restaurants and boutiques on Chestnut and Union Street, take a walk on the beach to the Golden Gate Bridge or rent a bike and ride across it while taking the ferry back, ride a cable car at Fisherman's Wharf or visit the de Young Museum or California Academy of Science in Golden Gate Park. The best of San Francisco is within easy reach.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished rental is located in Nob Hill. Just a short distance away from Union Square, the Westfield, the Embarcadero and Chinatown, this property is right in the center of a beautiful and active neighborhood. Its historic architecture now meets new styles of shopping and dining and an urban style of living and invites a diverse mix of residents to nest nearby. host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

name: Walk to BART & Glen Park
description: New Floors.  Beautiful Garden.  Perfect for 1-6 months stay.  Warm, cozy and sophisticated describes this unique 1908 Glen Park Victorian gem. Conveniently located by a BART station and tech shuttle stops within walking distance. Easy Hwy 101 and 280 access to downtown, the airport, and the South Bay.
neighborhood_overview:
Lying directly below the more popular Noe Valley neighborhood, Glen Park is a primarily residential neighborhood with a distinctly village-like vibe. To the west lies of Glen Park is the enormous Glen Canyon Park and to the north is Billy Goat Hill, which somewhat isolate this area from the rest of the city.

One major disadvantage of Glen Park is its frequent foggy weather, but what it lacks in sun it makes up for in nature. Billy Goat Hill in Glen Canyon Park is a particular delight, with a swing on a cliff overlooking the neighborhood. Penny Lane, Poppy Lane, and Ohlone Way are hidden dirt roads near the heart of Glen Park ripe for a magic day of exploration.

Conveniently located 2 blocks from Ocean Beach and a short walk to Golden Gate Park. It's steps away from the N-Judah MUNI line and 7 bus that connects you to downtown. A short walking distance to shops, restaurants, and grocery store. There's also an incredible gym called Muscle Beach that's only 1 block away where you can buy day passes.
neighborhood_overview: The Outer Sunset has so many hidden gems scattered throughout the neighborhood. It's one of the best places in the city to get a truly local experience. The Sunset is right next to Ocean Beach, but a bit of a trek to downtown. If you're looking for a quiet, neighborhood vibe with cute shops and restaurants, this is the place for you! There is a lot of free street parking in the neighborhood.
host_about:
Hello and welcome! My partner and co-host, Ray, and I love
the Sunset. Ray even grew up here.

The Sunset is one of San Franciso's hidden gems, in our humble opinion. It's a quiet neighborhood set against the backdrop of a beautiful and wild ocean. We love walking our dog Benny at the beach, and we're avid surfers, so you may see us in the shared foyer on occasion since we live in the upstairs unit.

name: Quiet, Cozy San Francisco Home
description:

Please note that the downstairs has a separate entrance - there is no interior staircase - and that is where one bedroom, bath, a hangout/games area, and washer/dryer are located.

Located in the heart of San Francisco's eclectic Mission District, our co-living space offers easy access to some of the city's best restaurants, bars, and shops. Whether you're here to explore the neighborhood's vibrant art scene or simply relax and unwind, our central location makes it easy!

Whether you're a solo traveler or a group of friends seeking affordable accommodations in the heart of San Francisco, our hostel offers the perfect blend of history, charm, and affordability.
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to the vibrant and culturally rich Mission District, located in the heart of San Francisco. This diverse neighborhood offers an authentic and captivating experience for our guests.

The Mission District is renowned for its colorful murals, which adorn the facades of buildings throughout the area. Take a leisurely stroll along Balmy Alley or Clarion Alley to marvel at the stunning street art that showcases the neighborhood's history and creative spirit.

Food enthusiasts will delight in the Mission District's thriving culinary scene. Explore the numerous taquerias, bakeries, and trendy restaurants that serve up a fusion of flavors from around the world. Whether you're craving authentic Mexican cuisine, innovative farm-to-table dishes, or delicious street food, the Mission District has something to satisfy every palate.

Shopping enthusiasts will find an array of unique boutiques, vintage stores, and independent shops along Valencia Street and Missio

name: Charming, Airy 3-Bedroom House by GG Park w Garage
description: This bright 3-bedroom house is on the second floor, has a dedicated garage with EV charging.  Stylishly furnished with flair. Hardwood floors throughout. Has a king, queen and two twin beds. Formal living room has a row of bay windows, a dedicated work desk and large mounted flatscreen. Formal dining room, charming wood trim, French doors. Big, modernized cook-in kitchen. One full bathroom with shower-over-tub. Skylights throughout for bright, airy feeling. GG Park within walking distance.
neighborhood_overview:
Sunset neighborhood, adjacent to Golden Gate Park. Few blocks to Sunset Boulevard. One-mile to Great Highway/Ocean Beach. Muni bus lines equi-distant from all directions of the home. Thoroughfare corridor at corner,
route to downtown SF within 30-minutes by car. Irving St commercial corridor for ease of dining, shopping: 2-mins by car, 5-10 minutes walking distance.
host_about:
'Not all who wander are lost.' I love this quote. 
I am that wanderer, incredibly lucky to be infected with the passion and audacity to travel often and solo. 
I was born and raised in San Francisco. I am a native. I love my city. I’ve watched it evolve. But I have also left it many times in my youth. I’ve left it to study abroad in France. Best decision of my college life! I backpacked solo around western Europe. 
I’ve left SF when I was in the military and stationed around our country. I’ve also driven as far north as Niagara Falls.
Career wise, I’ve spent over a decade in property management and rentals. I'm also a realtor. As a hobby, I write as often as possible, a pen and notebook on me at all times.
I am cursed with this blessing of being unceasingly interested in people. I love meeting people. I love hearing stories. And I love writing them. 
As I review my life’s experiences, I’ve come upon one very simple realization, that proclaimed secret of success. It is merely this: ‘Say what you will do and do what you will say.’
The prolific Seth Godin, talented blogger said creativity isn’t the most important part. What counts is being able to ship! Ship on time. And ship again. And again. And again.

name: Modern and Stylish Miraloma Park House
description: A comfortable, sleek, south facing, sunny house with very crisp lines. The home has two levels. The ingenious garage has EV charging, a giant flatscreen, a gym station and still enough room for parking. First floor has the primary bedroom with ensuite attached bathroom. Second main floor has the two-bedrooms, one-bath. An open concept living, dining, kitchen layout. Cook-in kitchen black shaker cabinets, s/s appliances. Walk-out deck with cityscape views and a BBQ grill. Extra driveway parking.
host_about:
'Not all who wander are lost.' I love this quote. 
I am that wanderer, incredibly lucky to be infected with the passion and audacity to travel often and solo. 
I was born and raised in San Francisco. I am a native. I love my city. I’ve watched it evolve. But I have also left it many times in my youth. I’ve left it to study abroad in France. Best decision of my college life! I backpacked solo around western Europe. 
I’ve left SF when I was in the military and stationed around our country. I’ve also driven as far north as Niagara Falls.
Career wise, I’ve spent over a decade in property management and rentals. I'm also a realtor. As a hobby, I write as often as possible, a pen and notebook on me at all times.
I am cursed with this blessing of being unceasingly interested in people. I love meeting people. I love hearing stories. And I love writing them. 
As I review my life’s experiences, I’ve come upon one very simple realization, that proclaimed secret of success. It is merely this: ‘Say what you will do and do what you will say.’
The prolific Seth Godin, talented blogger said creativity isn’t the most important part. What counts is being able to ship! Ship on time. And ship again. And again. And again.
